cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS

The paper introduces a new stochastic optimization method for over-parameterized networks, which is a common topic in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also provides theoretical analysis and convergence results, which suggests it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the method on several standard architectures of deep networks, including convolutional and fully connected networks, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper mentions its performance for convex kernel machines, which suggests it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
